---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "February 2026";
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - Poster Magic">
    <main class="min-h-screen bg-slate-950 py-20 px-4 md:px-8">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            <header class="mb-12 text-center">
                <h1
                    class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold bg-clip-text text-transparent bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-400 to-purple-500 mb-4"
                >
                    Poster Magic Terms of Service
                </h1>
                <p class="text-slate-400">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
            </header>

            <article
                class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none space-y-8 text-slate-300"
            >
                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        1. Acceptance of Terms
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        By using the Poster Magic application ("App"), you agree
                        to these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree
                        to these Terms, do not use the App.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        2. Description of Service
                    </h2>
                    <p>Poster Magic allows you to:</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                        <li>
                            Scan event posters to extract event details using AI
                        </li>
                        <li>Save events to your personal calendar</li>
                        <li>
                            Optionally share events with the Poster Magic
                            community
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        3. User Accounts
                    </h2>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                        <li>
                            You must be at least 13 years old to use this App
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            You are responsible for maintaining the security of
                            your account
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            You are responsible for all activity that occurs
                            under your account
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        4. Community Sharing & Content Guidelines
                    </h2>
                    <p>When sharing events publicly, you agree to:</p>

                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-2">
                        4.1 Accuracy
                    </h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                        <li>Only share accurate, real event information</li>
                        <li>
                            Not create fake, spam, or misleading event listings
                        </li>
                        <li>Verify event details before sharing</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-2">
                        4.2 Prohibited Content
                    </h3>
                    <p>You may NOT share content that:</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                        <li>
                            Is illegal, harmful, or promotes illegal activities
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Contains hate speech, discrimination, or harassment
                        </li>
                        <li>Is sexually explicit or pornographic</li>
                        <li>Promotes violence or dangerous activities</li>
                        <li>Infringes on intellectual property rights</li>
                        <li>Contains malware, spam, or phishing attempts</li>
                        <li>
                            Impersonates others or misrepresents your identity
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-2">
                        4.3 Content Moderation
                    </h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                        <li>
                            All shared content is subject to automated and
                            manual review
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Content that violates these guidelines may be
                            removed without notice
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Repeated violations may result in account
                            restrictions or termination
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        5. User Conduct
                    </h2>
                    <p>You agree NOT to:</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                        <li>Abuse, harass, or threaten other users</li>
                        <li>
                            Submit false reports against other users or events
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Attempt to circumvent content moderation systems
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Use automated tools to scrape or manipulate the
                            service
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Interfere with the proper functioning of the App
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        6. Reporting & Blocking
                    </h2>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                        <li>You may report events that violate these Terms</li>
                        <li>
                            You may block users whose content you do not wish to
                            see
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            False or abusive reporting may result in account
                            restrictions
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        7. Intellectual Property
                    </h2>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                        <li>You retain ownership of content you create</li>
                        <li>
                            By sharing events publicly, you grant Poster Magic a
                            license to display and distribute that content
                            within the App
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Poster Magic and its logos are trademarks of Poster
                            Magic
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        8. Privacy
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        Your use of the App is also governed by our Privacy
                        Policy at <a
                            href="/poster-magic-policy"
                            class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors"
                            >xondesk.com/poster-magic-policy</a
                        >
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        9. Disclaimers
                    </h2>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                        <li>
                            Event information is user-generated and may contain
                            errors
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Poster Magic does not guarantee the accuracy of
                            event details
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Poster Magic is not responsible for events that are
                            cancelled, rescheduled, or misrepresented
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            THE APP IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY
                            KIND
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        10. Limitation of Liability
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, POSTER MAGIC
                        SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL,
                        SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS
                        OF PROFITS OR REVENUES.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        11. Account Restrictions
                    </h2>
                    <p>Poster Magic reserves the right to:</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                        <li>Remove content that violates these Terms</li>
                        <li>
                            Restrict or terminate accounts that violate these
                            Terms
                        </li>
                        <li>Modify or discontinue the service at any time</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        12. Changes to Terms
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        We may update these Terms from time to time. Continued
                        use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of
                        the new Terms.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        13. Governing Law
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        These Terms shall be governed by the laws of the State
                        of California, United States.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        14. Contact
                    </h2>
                    <p>For questions about these Terms, contact us at:</p>
                    <div class="mt-4">
                        <a
                            href="mailto:support@postermagic.app"
                            class="text-xl text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors"
                            >support@postermagic.app</a
                        >
                    </div>
                </section>
            </article>

            <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-slate-800 text-center">
                <a
                    href="/"
                    class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors"
                    >‚Üê Back to Home</a
                >
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>
